        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>SECTION 3.  RIGHT OF FIRST REFUSAL
Art. 2625.  Right of first refusal
A party may agree that he will not sell a certain thing without first offering it to a certain person.  The right given to the latter in such a case is a right of first refusal that may be enforced by specific performance.</p>
        </content>
